00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:21,384
Wherever you are,
we send you our love.

491
00:31:04,210 --> 00:31:05,472
[CRYING]

492
00:31:18,398 --> 00:31:19,703
Thank you.

493
00:31:24,970 --> 00:31:27,711
When are you gonna stop
coming in here asking me
the same question?

494
00:31:27,755 --> 00:31:29,888
When you
give me an answer.

495
00:31:29,931 --> 00:31:32,934
Well, why don't you
come in during Catherine's
shift and ask her?

496
00:31:32,978 --> 00:31:35,241
Because Catherine will
always side with Mike.

497
00:31:35,284 --> 00:31:37,243
And what makes you
think I won't?

498
00:31:37,286 --> 00:31:39,810
[SIGHS]
I think sooner or later
you're gonna realize

499
00:31:39,854 --> 00:31:42,639
that he's just
stringing you along,
like he did me.

500
00:31:42,683 --> 00:31:44,641
You don't know what
you're talking about.

501
00:31:44,685 --> 00:31:46,426
Mike loves me.

502
00:31:46,469 --> 00:31:48,167
He's gonna send for me.

503
00:31:48,210 --> 00:31:50,952
Hey, if that's
what you want,
I hope you get it.

504
00:31:50,996 --> 00:31:52,911
I just want my son back.

505
00:31:52,954 --> 00:31:54,738
You've gotta stop
coming here.

506
00:31:54,782 --> 00:31:58,177
Look, I don't know
what else to do.

507
00:31:58,220 --> 00:32:00,440
My son means
everything to me.

508
00:32:00,483 --> 00:32:04,923
I've never begged for
anything in my life,
and I'm begging you.

509
00:32:04,966 --> 00:32:06,533
Please, help me.

510
00:32:09,275 --> 00:32:12,800
They're somewhere in Oregon,
and that is all I know.

511
00:32:14,758 --> 00:32:16,935
VAN: Lael?

512
00:32:16,978 --> 00:32:19,981
Yeah, I'm here.

513
00:32:20,025 --> 00:32:22,984
Oh. Hey, I talked
to the police
and the investigator,

514
00:32:23,028 --> 00:32:24,899
and they're on it.Great.

515
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:26,683
What are you doing?I know Mike.

516
00:32:26,727 --> 00:32:28,424
He loves to fish,
and I know his two
favorite rivers.

517
00:32:28,468 --> 00:32:30,600
Well, that's great.
Listen, I'll pass along
the information.

518
00:32:30,644 --> 00:32:32,167
I just can't sit
around anymore.

519
00:32:32,211 --> 00:32:34,126
Well, why don't you
wait for the weekend?

520
00:32:34,169 --> 00:32:36,476
I'll go with you.I can't wait for
the weekend. Come on.

521
00:32:38,739 --> 00:32:40,741
What about your business?

522
00:32:40,784 --> 00:32:42,569
Julie can make
the deliveries.

523
00:32:42,612 --> 00:32:44,484
Mike sees you,
he'll run.

524
00:32:50,316 --> 00:32:52,448
All right.

525
00:32:52,492 --> 00:32:53,972
I'll take care
of things on this end.

526
00:32:54,015 --> 00:32:57,018
Just promise me
that you'll be careful.

527
00:32:57,062 --> 00:32:59,455
I promise.

528
00:32:59,499 --> 00:33:01,457
I'm gonna find my son.

529
00:33:45,675 --> 00:33:47,808
Excuse me.
Have you seen
this boy?

530
00:33:50,376 --> 00:33:51,420
No, I haven't. Sorry.

531
00:33:52,595 --> 00:33:53,944
[INAUDIBLE]

532
00:33:57,644 --> 00:33:59,124
[INAUDIBLE]

533
00:34:32,983 --> 00:34:35,682
Pretty day.

534
00:34:35,725 --> 00:34:38,467
Yeah. I guess it is.

535
00:34:38,511 --> 00:34:40,817
I'm looking
for my son.

536
00:34:44,212 --> 00:34:46,693
Never had one myself.
Never got married.

537
00:34:50,436 --> 00:34:52,220
How come you're
looking for him?

538
00:34:52,264 --> 00:34:55,223
My ex-husband kidnapped him
after I was awarded custody.

539
00:34:56,311 --> 00:34:58,139
Sorry to hear that.

540
00:34:58,183 --> 00:35:00,402
Yeah, I was really hoping
you'd seen him.

541
00:35:00,446 --> 00:35:02,839
I've been looking for
a long time and, uh,

542
00:35:02,883 --> 00:35:04,406
well, this is just
the kind of place
he loves.

543
00:35:06,452 --> 00:35:09,672
What sort of...
Sort of fella is
your husband?

544
00:35:09,716 --> 00:35:13,328
Now's not
the best time to ask
if you want a fair answer.

545
00:35:13,372 --> 00:35:15,417
Thanks anyway.

546
00:35:18,159 --> 00:35:20,901
Your husband and son
are scheduled

547
00:35:20,944 --> 00:35:23,208
for an all-day trip on
Saturday.

548
00:35:23,251 --> 00:35:24,774
You saw Ace?

549
00:35:24,818 --> 00:35:27,081
Was he all right?
He's got severe asthma.

550
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:28,996
Well, far as
I could tell.

551
00:35:29,039 --> 00:35:30,128
Can I use your phone?

552
00:35:30,171 --> 00:35:33,174
Yeah. It's on the wall.

553
00:35:33,218 --> 00:35:36,569
[RINGING]

554
00:35:36,612 --> 00:35:38,179
[SIGHS] Van Stein.

555
00:35:38,223 --> 00:35:40,181
OPERATOR:
You have a collect call
from Lael Pritcher.

556
00:35:40,225 --> 00:35:43,793
Um, yeah.
I'll accept the charges.

557
00:35:43,837 --> 00:35:45,012
Lael, hi.

558
00:35:45,055 --> 00:35:46,361
LAEL: Hey,
I've got great news.

559
00:35:46,405 --> 00:35:48,146
I just found out
where Mike and Ace are.

560
00:35:48,189 --> 00:35:50,452
You're kidding.
That's great!

561
00:35:50,496 --> 00:35:52,367
Where are you?I'm in Steveston.

562
00:35:52,411 --> 00:35:54,195
Okay, look,
I'll be out there
around 6:00.

563
00:35:54,239 --> 00:35:56,806
You go check into a motel.
And don't leave the room.

564
00:35:56,850 --> 00:35:58,199
Don't leave the room
for anything.

565
00:35:58,243 --> 00:36:00,375
Remember, if Mike
sees you, he'll run.

566
00:36:00,419 --> 00:36:02,812
I know.
I know he will.
I understand.

567
00:36:02,856 --> 00:36:05,946
Great. Remember,
call me, let me know
where you're staying.

568
00:36:05,989 --> 00:36:06,990
Okay, I will.

569
00:36:08,601 --> 00:36:10,124
Thank you, Mister...

570
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:12,474
Uh, Solomon.
Just Solomon.

571
00:36:12,518 --> 00:36:14,781
Solomon.
Thanks, Solomon.

572
00:36:17,218 --> 00:36:18,698
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

573
00:36:53,428 --> 00:36:56,344
Where have you been?
I've been so worried.

574
00:36:56,388 --> 00:36:58,303
My bike broke down in
the middle of nowhere.

575
00:36:58,346 --> 00:37:00,261
It took a while to fix.

576
00:37:00,305 --> 00:37:01,828
You rode your bike
in this rain?

577
00:37:01,871 --> 00:37:04,265
Listen, I need to warm up,
and then we can fight, okay?

578
00:37:04,309 --> 00:37:06,659
Where's the shower?

579
00:37:06,702 --> 00:37:07,877
It's in there.

580
00:37:07,921 --> 00:37:09,879
Thanks.

581
00:37:09,923 --> 00:37:11,838
Just don't use
my toothbrush.

582
00:37:24,067 --> 00:37:25,808
I sure hope it stops.

583
00:37:27,332 --> 00:37:29,551
Well, we'll just have
to wait and see.

584
00:37:32,946 --> 00:37:34,208
What's the matter?

585
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:36,906
I think I need
to sit down.

586
00:37:38,908 --> 00:37:41,346
Lael,

587
00:37:41,389 --> 00:37:42,695
when's the last time
you ate?

588
00:37:42,738 --> 00:37:44,914
Oh, I'm not sure.

589
00:37:44,958 --> 00:37:46,220
Did you eat today?

590
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:49,310
Um, yesterday?

591
00:37:49,354 --> 00:37:52,313
Well, there's nothing open.
We'll get you something
to eat in the morning.

592
00:37:52,357 --> 00:37:53,880
Get in there.
Come on. Get in bed.

593
00:37:53,923 --> 00:37:55,316
Okay.

594
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:57,318
[SIGHS]

595
00:37:57,362 --> 00:37:59,146
Unbelievable.

596
00:37:59,189 --> 00:38:02,845
Now, look. We'll just talk about
everything tomorrow, all right?

597
00:38:02,889 --> 00:38:05,544
Now, I'm gonna sleep
here tonight. Okay?

598
00:38:05,587 --> 00:38:10,331
There's nobody in the office.
I'm too tired to go looking
for another room.

599
00:38:10,375 --> 00:38:12,246
I guarantee

600
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:16,903
I've got nothing on
my mind but sleep.

601
00:38:16,946 --> 00:38:18,513
All right?

602
00:38:18,557 --> 00:38:19,732
All right.

603
00:38:30,395 --> 00:38:32,397
[PHONE RINGING]

604
00:38:41,406 --> 00:38:44,757
Hello?Hi, it's Solomon.
They canceled. I'm sorry.

605
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,149
Thanks.

606
00:38:49,588 --> 00:38:51,329
What? What happened?

607
00:38:53,156 --> 00:38:55,071
[SOBBING]
Mike canceled.

608
00:39:06,474 --> 00:39:08,998
Maybe he'll reschedule.

609
00:39:09,042 --> 00:39:10,478
But when?

610
00:39:12,785 --> 00:39:14,482
This is driving me nuts!

611
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,660
Ace is here,
it's a small town.

612
00:39:18,704 --> 00:39:21,402
He could be in the room
next door.

613
00:39:21,446 --> 00:39:23,796
It's time to turn it
over to the police.

614
00:39:23,839 --> 00:39:25,580
They don't do anything.

615
00:39:25,624 --> 00:39:27,452
You said it yourself.
It's a small town.

616
00:39:27,495 --> 00:39:29,454
They ask a couple
of questions, bingo!

617
00:39:29,497 --> 00:39:31,499
They know where
the strangers are.

618
00:39:35,155 --> 00:39:37,418
[SIGHS] Look,

619
00:39:37,462 --> 00:39:40,334
I've got a court date
I've gotta be back for.

620
00:39:40,378 --> 00:39:41,814
Why don't we go home,
we'll regroup,

621
00:39:41,857 --> 00:39:42,945
we'll come back
in a couple of days.

622
00:39:42,989 --> 00:39:44,817
I'm not leaving.

623
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:48,124
I can't leave you
here by yourself.
It's too depressing.

624
00:39:48,168 --> 00:39:53,434
The grade school is doing
"The Wonderful Wizard of Oz"
tonight.

625
00:39:53,478 --> 00:39:56,524
If Ace has seen the poster,
he'll be there.

626
00:40:01,921 --> 00:40:03,096
I hope.

627
00:40:05,315 --> 00:40:06,229
All right.

628
00:40:09,102 --> 00:40:11,931
"The Scarecrow,
the Tin Woodman
and the Lion

629
00:40:11,974 --> 00:40:14,455
"thanked the Good Witch
for her kindness.

630
00:40:14,499 --> 00:40:16,849
"Then it was
Dorothy's turn.

631
00:40:16,892 --> 00:40:18,938
"'You are as good
as you are beautiful,

632
00:40:18,981 --> 00:40:22,332
"'but you have not yet
told me how to get back
to Kansas.'

633
00:40:22,376 --> 00:40:25,901
"'Your silver shoes
will carry you there,'
replied Glinda.

634
00:40:25,945 --> 00:40:30,645
"'If I had known their power,
you could have gone back
the very first day.'

635
00:40:30,689 --> 00:40:35,781
"'But then I would not
have had my wonderful brains,'
cried the Scarecrow.

636
00:40:35,824 --> 00:40:38,784
"'And I should not have
had my lovely heart.'

637
00:40:38,827 --> 00:40:42,483
"'And I would've
been a coward forever,'
declared the Lion.

638
00:40:42,527 --> 00:40:43,963
"'And no beast
in the forest[BARKING]

639
00:40:44,006 --> 00:40:45,965
"'would've had a good
word to say to me.'

640
00:40:47,401 --> 00:40:49,664
"Dorothy looks
at her friends.

641
00:40:49,708 --> 00:40:51,927
"'I'm glad I was
of use to you,

642
00:40:51,971 --> 00:40:54,756
"'but now that
each of you have
what you most desired,

643
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:56,845
"'I think I should
like to go back.'"

644
00:40:59,195 --> 00:41:01,502
"'Take me home to
Aunt Em in Kansas.'"

645
00:41:01,546 --> 00:41:05,637
"Aunt Em had just come out
of the house when she saw
Dorothy running toward her.

646
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:10,511
"'My darling child!'
she cried, holding
the little girl in her arms.

647
00:41:10,555 --> 00:41:12,774
"'Where in the world
did you come from?'

648
00:41:12,818 --> 00:41:15,429
"'From the Land of Oz,'
said Dorothy,[BARKING]

649
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:19,172
'where I met a tin woodman,
a scarecrow, and a lion.

650
00:41:19,215 --> 00:41:21,348
'And here is Toto, too.

651
00:41:21,391 --> 00:41:24,525
'And, oh, Aunt Em,
I'm so happy
to be home again!"

652
00:41:24,569 --> 00:41:26,179
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

653
00:41:31,663 --> 00:41:33,969
Excuse me. Hello.

654
00:41:35,231 --> 00:41:36,319
WOMAN: Stop her!

655
00:41:36,363 --> 00:41:38,234
[ALL CLAMORING]

656
00:41:38,278 --> 00:41:39,627
Stop her!

657
00:41:39,671 --> 00:41:43,370
Oh, my God!That's my son!
That's my son!

658
00:41:43,413 --> 00:41:45,198
That's our daughter.

659
00:41:45,241 --> 00:41:48,331
I'm... I'm so sorry.
I thought that was
Ace in there.

660
00:41:48,375 --> 00:41:49,985
I thought it was
my little boy...

661
00:41:50,029 --> 00:41:52,161
Bill, just call the cops.
Lady tried to take our kid.

662
00:41:52,205 --> 00:41:53,249
Okay. Come on.

663
00:41:53,293 --> 00:41:54,816
Oh, my God.

664
00:41:54,860 --> 00:41:56,426
MR. McQUINN:
The lady just grabbed her!

665
00:42:06,306 --> 00:42:09,744
LAEL: I've already told you,
I'm not a child molester.

666
00:42:09,788 --> 00:42:13,879
I was looking for my son,
and I made a terrible mistake.

667
00:42:13,922 --> 00:42:15,968
It's pretty hard to
mistake a girl for a boy.

668
00:42:16,011 --> 00:42:18,623
But she was
wearing a costume.

669
00:42:18,666 --> 00:42:21,364
I got a call about you
yesterday morning
from a man

670
00:42:21,408 --> 00:42:23,236
claiming to be
your lawyer.

671
00:42:23,279 --> 00:42:25,804
He said that your ex-husband
had your son around
here somewhere.

672
00:42:25,847 --> 00:42:28,894
Well, then, you know
I'm telling the truth.
Why didn't you say so?

673
00:42:28,937 --> 00:42:30,809
You tried to kidnap
a child last night.

674
00:42:30,852 --> 00:42:34,508
Look, would you please
just try my lawyer
one more time?

675
00:42:34,552 --> 00:42:36,815
I told you,
there's no answer.

676
00:42:36,858 --> 00:42:38,468
Bring them in.

677
00:42:49,262 --> 00:42:51,351
Is this the woman you saw
trying to take your child?

678
00:42:53,048 --> 00:42:55,094
Yes, sir.Yes, yes, it is.

679
00:42:55,137 --> 00:42:57,357
BECK: Are you ready
to press charges?

680
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,924
Yes.

681
00:42:58,967 --> 00:43:00,578
Look, I'm really sorry

682
00:43:00,621 --> 00:43:02,710
about what happened
last night.

683
00:43:02,754 --> 00:43:06,540
You see, I've been
searching for my little boy
for a very long time.

684
00:43:06,584 --> 00:43:08,803
And Toto's his
favorite character.

685
00:43:08,847 --> 00:43:13,460
So when I saw
your little girl's hair
up under that costume,

686
00:43:13,503 --> 00:43:16,115
I guess
I wanted so much
for it to be Ace,

687
00:43:16,158 --> 00:43:18,813
I just decided it was.

688
00:43:18,857 --> 00:43:21,555
I'm so sorry
I frightened
your little girl.

689
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:24,645
And I'm sorry
I frightened you.

690
00:43:59,419 --> 00:44:00,768
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

691
00:44:04,163 --> 00:44:05,643
Who is it?Van!

692
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:09,995
Hi.Hi.

693
00:44:10,038 --> 00:44:13,433
Can I come in?Oh, sure.

694
00:44:13,476 --> 00:44:16,088
What are you
doing here?

695
00:44:16,131 --> 00:44:19,178
How many times
do I have to tell you,
I'm worried about you.

696
00:44:19,221 --> 00:44:20,701
What about work?

697
00:44:20,745 --> 00:44:23,269
I got someone to cover for me.
I wanted to be here.

698
00:44:23,312 --> 00:44:25,532
So, tell me what
happened at the play.
Did you see Ace?

699
00:44:25,575 --> 00:44:28,013
[SIGHS] You're not gonna
believe what happened.

700
00:44:28,056 --> 00:44:30,711
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

701
00:44:30,755 --> 00:44:32,234
Who's there?

702
00:44:32,278 --> 00:44:34,367
Solomon.

703
00:44:34,410 --> 00:44:35,716
Hi, Solomon.

704
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:37,500
Uh, hope I'm not
bothering you.

705
00:44:37,544 --> 00:44:39,720
No. Not at all.
Come in.

706
00:44:39,764 --> 00:44:42,331
Solomon, this is Van Stein,
the lawyer I told you about.

707
00:44:42,375 --> 00:44:44,725
Ah, pleased to...
Pleased to meet you.Pleased to meet you.

708
00:44:44,769 --> 00:44:47,685
Uh, it's probably nothing,
but I thought I should
tell you.

709
00:44:47,728 --> 00:44:50,209
A good friend of mine,
a doctor, he said
he's been treating a boy

710
00:44:50,252 --> 00:44:53,647
with the worst case of
asthma he's ever seen.

711
00:44:53,691 --> 00:44:56,650
Now, you said
your son had it,
so I asked who it was,

712
00:44:56,694 --> 00:44:58,260
and he said I wouldn't know

713
00:44:58,304 --> 00:45:00,872
because he and his father
were new to the area.

714
00:45:00,915 --> 00:45:03,483
You wanna check it out?
They're at the Roadway Cabins.

715
00:45:03,526 --> 00:45:05,093
That's just half a mile
up the road.

716
00:45:05,137 --> 00:45:08,357
Oh, Solomon!
Thanks so much.

717
00:45:08,401 --> 00:45:10,751
I hope it's him.

718
00:45:10,795 --> 00:45:12,274
Thank you.

719
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:15,930
Bye.Bye.

720
00:45:15,974 --> 00:45:17,366
It's gotta be them.

721
00:45:17,410 --> 00:45:19,673
Well, we'll sure
as hell find out.

722
00:45:23,546 --> 00:45:25,418
Sheriff Beck, please.

723
00:45:25,461 --> 00:45:27,812
Oh, hey,
wait, wait, no!
Hang up.

724
00:45:27,855 --> 00:45:30,205
We've gotta be real sure
before we call him.

725
00:45:30,249 --> 00:45:31,816
Well, that's his job,
to find out.

726
00:45:31,859 --> 00:45:33,426
He thinks I'm
a child molester.

727
00:45:33,469 --> 00:45:36,037
Say what?I went to the play
last night,

728
00:45:36,081 --> 00:45:39,911
and I was so sure
it was Ace up there
dressed like Toto,

729
00:45:39,954 --> 00:45:42,000
so I tried to get him
to leave with me,

730
00:45:42,043 --> 00:45:45,917
and it turned out
it was a little girl.

731
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:47,788
They thought I was
trying to kidnap her.

732
00:45:47,832 --> 00:45:50,486
So I was arrested
and spent the night
in jail.

733
00:45:50,530 --> 00:45:53,315
[CHUCKLES] Ouch.

